In his Memorial Day address at Arlington National Cemetery, President Joe Biden honored the fallen heroes who sacrificed their lives in service to America. He expressed empathy towards the families of those who have lost loved ones and emphasized the pride and honor felt by both the fallen soldiers and their families. Biden highlighted the ongoing struggle for democracy, both at home and around the world, and stressed the importance of preserving and strengthening democratic values. He called for the defense of democracy and the protection of voting rights, a free press, and the rule of law. Biden acknowledged the imperfections of American democracy but emphasized the progress made in creating a more inclusive and just society. He emphasized the need for unity and the duty to carry forward the legacy of liberty and union. Biden concluded his address by urging Americans to dedicate themselves to the ongoing work of democracy and to keep the faith in the pursuit of a free, fair, and strong nation.